Auto Loan Payment CalculatorLoan amount$Annual interest rate%Term--Select--1 year 2 years3 years4 years5 years6 years7 years8 years9 years10 years
    Before buying a new or used car, it's likely that many questions will arise, particularly in 
    regard to financing. For example:What will the monthly payment be?How will the loan term affect the monthly payment (e.g., 3-year, 6-year)?How will the interest rate affect the monthly payment?This calculator can be used to answer these questions and illustrate key issues.
    Enter the required values to calculate the monthly payment, and select the desired output. An annual amortization table and two charts comparing principal and interest payments can be generated.
    




Auto Loan Payment Calculator ResultsMonthly payment: $359.37Total payments: $21,562Total interest: $1,562Your monthly payment is: $359
        This chart shows the part of your yearly payments that is applied to interest and the part that is applied to principal.
      
        Over time, though your payments stay the same, the interest portion decreases, and the principal portion increases.
      Over the term of your loan you have total payments of $21,562, of which $1,562 is interest payments.View TableStart OverAssumptions
      Calculation assumes constant monthly payments over the life of the loan, monthly calculation of interest on the remaining unpaid principal, and no prepayment. Only principal and interest payments are included; property tax and/or insurance payments are not included.
    




















